item.title: This guy gets it
item.description: Buddy of mine found himself in a similar situation with his Grandson. Grandson was a Freshman and was attacked by a Junior in the cafeteria - takes roughly 15-20 punches while "Adult Monitors" stood and watched but didn't intervene. My buddy's grandson has an Uncle that takes him to BJJ classes though...grandson lifts the bully, bodyslams him, and punches him ONE TIME which immediately ends the attack. Grandson ended up suspended for 5 days because he's "supposed to assume a turtle position until adults arrive to help." My buddy is a retired Marine. He took his grandson for ice cream and they hung out while he was suspended. My own son and his classmates were all being hit by another classmate in his kindergarten class. The kid nearly choked another child into unconsciousness. Teachers explained away the assaults with "he's a troubled child" and just put him in time out each time. I told my son to beat the snot out of the kid if he touched him again. My wife said he'd get suspended for fighting and I said we'd go to fucking Disney World if they suspended him for defending himself. Teach your kids not to start fights, but to end them.

So, instead of finding the one thing in here you don't like and commenting only on that, also comment about something you DID like. Balance the negativity. Love you long time. So, I made a discord server. It's a relaxed environment where you can take/donate memes to the cause, play trivia twice a week, chat about lots of topics or about nothing at all. We also have Jack Box game night and are setting up movie night! Very laid back/relaxed vibe.
